==English==
===Pronunciation===
*fyo͞od, /fjuːd/, /<tt>fju:d</tt>/
*:[[Rhymes:English:-uːd|Rhymes: -uːd]]

===Noun===
'''feud''' ([[feuds]])

# long-standing [[hostility]]
#: ''The two men began to '''feud''' after one of them got a job promotion and the other thought he was more qualified.''
# (''professional wrestling slang'') In professional wrestling, when two rival [[wrestler]]s engage in a series of [[matches]]; often has an [[angle]] tied to it.

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[sukuriita]] (''family feud'')
*Telugu: [[తగాదా]] (tagAdA)

===Intransitive verb===
'''to feud''' ([[feuds]], [[feuded]], [[feuding]])

# to carry on a feud

